work.name: Oakland City University
work.summary: Trained student leader who lives in a campus residence hall and supports residents by building community, enforcing housing policies, and serving as a resource for academic, personal, and social needs
highlights: Organized social, educational, and recreational activities for residents.
Mediated conflicts between residents and enforced university policies.

volunteer.summary: Helping out with subjects such as Math, English, and Science to a class of second-grade students. Created lesson plans and activities to engage students and promote learning.
highlights: Improved students' academic performance and confidence through personalized instruction and support.

projects.name: Adventure Game
projects.summary: A text-based adventure game where players navigate through a series of rooms, collect items, and solve puzzles to reach the end goal.
highlights: Implemented room navigation, item collection, and puzzle-solving mechanics using Python.
Designed an engaging storyline and multiple endings based on player choices.
